This crisis is a political stress test. The real question is about the political will of #Europeans to solve this crisis together.
The determination of Germany to stick to the Euro was a decisive factor.
Germany under the leadership of Chancellor Merkel has shown this political will.
The Euro greatly benefits German companies and jobs. Germany profited the most from a virtuous circle triggered by the Euro.
The passimg from the D-Mark to the Euro is the most concrete symbol of German and European unification being the two sides of the same coin.
When we talk about the rebalancing  we are not talking about weakening the competitiveness of the German economy.
But Germany could do more to enable others to bring in their respective assets, e.g. through free and unhindered access to service markets.
Moving towards political union, step by step, starting with completion of banking union. Germany has an imminently crucial role in this.
I know very well that all main political forces in Germany have that commitment to Europe. My message to you is simple: Keep it.
In a globalised world, sovereignty pooled means power gained for every member of the EU, not power lost.
